In this article, it is reported that President Obama spoke with King Hamad bin Isa Al-Khalifa of Bahrain to discuss the ongoing situation in Bahrain. President Obama condemned the violence used against peaceful protesters and urged the government of Bahrain to show restraint and hold those responsible for the violence accountable. The President emphasized that the stability of Bahrain depends on respecting the universal rights of its people and implementing meaningful reform that addresses the aspirations of all Bahrainis.